Total length 4.05 Carapace (
Fig. 1A
): 2.21 long, 1.43 wide; yellow-brown, narrow dark median band and dark discolourations and spots in cephalic area; areas around eyes black. Eyes: AME 0.18, ALE 0.13, PME 0.14, PLE 0.09; row of eyes: AME 0.40, PME 0.34, PLE 083. Sternum (
Fig. 1B
): 0.98 long, 0.72 wide; yellow-brown; with dark irregular spots, denser towards margins. Labium (
Fig. 1B
): wider than long; basal half light brown with darker pigmentation, anterior part forms a nearly semi-circular white rim. Chelicerae (
Fig. 1B
): yellow-brown; three promarginal teeth, with the central one largest; three retromarginal teeth, with the basal smallest.

Pedipalp (
Figs. 1C, D
; 
3A, B
